<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-SEARS PRESIDENT ARCHIE R. BOE DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Archie R. Boe, former president of Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co. and Allstate 
Insurance Co., has died of cancer at age 67. 
</P>
<P>
Boe, who joined Allstate in 1941 and worked for the insurance company or its 
parent, Sears, until retirement in 1984, died Monday at Northwestern Memorial 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
"He was one of the first corporate executives to adapt long-range planning, 
known as strategic planning, into the corporate world," said Ray Ewing, a 
former Allstate spokesman who worked with Boe for 20 years. 
</P>
<P>
Known mostly as a car insurer, Allstate expanded into other areas of coverage 
in 1957 under Boe's leadership. 
</P>
<P>
Boe was named president of Allstate in 1966 and chairman and chief executive 
officer in 1972. In 1982 he was named president of Sears, a post he held for 
two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
