<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHILD ABUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to Donna Caffrey's letter ("Addicted Baby," Dec. 28): 
</P>
<P>
Yes, it is very sad that Michael Hudson was born addicted to cocaine. What is 
even sadder is Caffrey's statement that "giving birth to a sick baby and having 
him taken away from her" is punishment enough for Toni Hudson, the infant's 
mother. 
</P>
<P>
This woman knew as do all potential drug addicts that cocaine is addictive. 
Willingly abusing drugs is not a disease, it is a choice. Toni Hudson of her 
own free will decided to take cocaine. There was no disease to impair her 
judgment or cause her to take it against her will. The only disease she is 
suffering from is stupidity. 
</P>
<P>
She is guilty of child abuse from the moment she decided not to take or use 
birth control. There is enough information available to her and other potential 
drug addicts to warn them against the dangers of drug abuse, and the harmful 
effects to pregnant women and their unborn children. Again, it was her choice 
not to use birth control and her choice to use cocaine. 
</P>
<P>
Isn't being born to a mother who totally disregarded his health and welfare and 
being placed in a hospital to suffer during his young life punishment enough 
for Michael? 
</P>
<P>
SANDRA ORTIZ-LOPEMAN 
</P>
<P>
Downey 
</P>
</TEXT>
