<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOMEYNESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prof. Laurence Goldstein's lament ("Ground Down by High-Rise Fever," Editorial 
Page, Dec. 24), about the disappearance of the old-fashioned homeyness of a 
city, is easy to sympathize with. Others may see beauty in endless towers and 
little else. Thus, I recall a lady's remark as she confronted the venerable 
skyscraper in New York, the Woolworth Building. She exclaimed, "My! How 
heavenly!" Not all would agree. Be that as it may, I offer one small 
suggestion; more greenery to the scenery, please! 
