<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
SIMI VALLEY DEFENSE THWARTED BY CHANNEL ISLANDS' TAUAUA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite Simi Valley's double- and triple-teaming defense, sophomore center Sal 
Tauaua of Channel Islands scored a game-high 26 points to lead the Lady Raiders 
to a 68-58 victory Tuesday in a Marmonte League opener at Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Shannon Solway had 14 points, 15 rebounds and 6 assists for Simi Valley (9-5 
overall). 
</P>
<P>
In other games: 
</P>
<P>
La Reina 61, Moorpark 22 -- All 11 players scored for La Reina in the 
Tri-Valley League opener at La Reina. 
</P>
<P>
Heather Freeman led La Reina (6-6) with 13 points. Moorpark, which trailed, 
38-8, at halftime, failed to score in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff 47, Burbank 40 -- Seniors Lisa Negrete and Andja Vucurevic had 12 and 
10 points, respectively, to lead Bell-Jeff (11-3) to the nonleague win at home. 
</P>
<P>
Senior forward Jennifer Helsley had 18 points for Burbank (1-8). 
</P>
<P>
Alemany 56, Antelope Valley 44 -- Alemany came back from a 5-point halftime 
deficit to beat Antelope Valley in a nonleague game. Andrea Hoffman had 23 
points and Sylvia Castaneda had 10 to lead Alemany. 
</P>
