<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUSTRALIA FOOTBALL TOUR IN WORKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pat Blackburn, football coach at Alemany High, is assembling a team for a pair 
of exhibition games in Australia this summer under the sponsorship of the New 
Zealand American Football League. 
</P>
<P>
The team is open to high school players who will graduate this year. Ten teams 
from 10 states will play 2 games each during the trip, which runs from June 30 
to July 17. The California team will play Nevada in Sydney and then again in 
Brisbane. 
</P>
<P>
Players must assume the $1,300 cost of the trip. The fee covers air fare, hotel 
accommodations for 10 days, all meals and a 4-day stay in Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for applications is April 1. 
</P>
<P>
For further information, call Blackburn at 818-898-0025. 
</P>
