<P>
The Treasury sold $7.2 billion of new three-month bills at an average discount 
rate of 8.24%, up from 8.22% last week. Another $7.2 billion of new six-month 
bills was sold at an average discount rate of 8.37%, up from 8.33% last week. 
The rates were the highest since three-month bills sold for 8.41% on March 25, 
