<P>
Country singer Johnny Cash, who underwent a double heart bypass on Dec. 19, was 
released Tuesday from Baptist Hospital in Nashville. Although Cash, 56, had 
suffered lung problems after the surgery, a hospital spokeswoman said the 
complications were not unusual and the doctors would not have released Cash "if 
everything wasn't OK." Cash described the double-bypass as "a great, 
soul-searching experience" and said he'll thank God for bringing him through 
the operation by making a record of Bible readings with another heart patient, 
Waylon Jennings. ALEENE MacMINN 
