<P>
 MAN, 24, JAILED IN FATAL HIT-AND-RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old man was in jail Tuesday as the suspected hit-and-run driver who 
killed a young boy and critically injured his cousin on New Year's Day, Long 
Beach police said. 
</P>
<P>
Louis Fitzgerald Burroughs, 24, was taken into custody Monday afternoon after 
someone telephoned police to tell them where to find the driver of a gold 
Lincoln Continental that struck the boy, So Den Taing, 6, and girl, Kanika El, 
5, at Alamitos and 17th streets, Lt. Mike Hill said. 
</P>
